---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import LabNav from '../../../components/LabNav.astro'
import { getChallengeById } from '../../../data/challenges'

const challenge = getChallengeById('dns-exfil')!
---
<Layout title={challenge.title} description={challenge.description}>
  <LabNav />
  <main class="shell challenge-page">
    <div class="breadcrumb mono">
      <a href="/lab">foil/lab</a> / <a href="/lab/challenges">challenges</a> / {challenge.id}
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <div class="header-badges">
        <span class={`badge badge-${challenge.difficulty}`}>
          <span class="dot" style="background:#41d07f"></span>
          {challenge.difficulty}
        </span>
        <span class="badge badge-cat">{challenge.category}</span>
        <span class="badge badge-cat mono">{challenge.points} pts</span>
      </div>
      <h1>{challenge.title}</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">{challenge.description}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div class="main-col">
        <section class="card">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— scenario</h2>
          <div class="scenario-body" set:html={challenge.scenario.replace(/\*\*(.+?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>').replace(/\n/g, '<br />')} />
        </section>

        <section class="card">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— challenge file</h2>
          {challenge.files.map(f => (
            <a href={f.path} download class="file-row" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              <span class="file-icon">⬇</span>
              <span class="file-info">
                <span class="file-name mono">{f.name}</span>
                <span class="file-size mono">{f.size}</span>
              </span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </section>

        <section class="card writeup-card">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— write-up</h2>
          <p class="writeup-teaser">The full write-up explains the DNS exfiltration technique, how to detect it with Wireshark / grep, and how FoilGuard defends against newly-registered domains used in this pattern.</p>
          <details class="writeup-reveal">
            <summary class="mono">reveal write-up (spoilers)</summary>
            <div class="writeup-content">
              <h3>Step 1 — spot the anomaly</h3>
              <p>Filter the log to show only queries from <code>192.168.1.42</code>. Of those, the vast majority go to <code>*.company.local</code> or known SaaS hosts. Four queries stand out: they all go to subdomains of <code>exfil.badactor.cc</code>, a domain you wouldn't expect to see in any normal business log.</p>

              <h3>Step 2 — collect the subdomain labels</h3>
              <p>Each subdomain label follows the pattern <code>&lt;hex-chunk&gt;.&lt;sequence-number&gt;.exfil.badactor.cc</code>. Sort by sequence number and extract the hex chunks in order:</p>
              <pre><code>1: 464f494c7b6330
2: 763372745f6368
3: 346e6e336c5f64
4: 6e735f37787d</code></pre>

              <h3>Step 3 — decode</h3>
              <p>Concatenate: <code>464f494c7b6330763372745f6368346e6e336c5f646e735f37787d</code></p>
              <p>Decode as ASCII:</p>
              <pre><code>python3 -c "print(bytes.fromhex('464f494c7b6330763372745f6368346e6e336c5f646e735f37787d').decode())"</code></pre>
              <p>Result: <code>FOIL&#123;c0v3rt_ch4nn3l_dns_7x&#125;</code></p>

              <h3>Why this works as an attack</h3>
              <p>DNS is almost never blocked outbound and is rarely inspected in depth. By encoding data into subdomain labels (max 63 chars each), an attacker can exfiltrate data as long as they control a domain that resolves DNS queries — the "answers" don't even matter, because the data rides in the queries themselves.</p>
              <p>Detection signals: unusual external domains receiving queries from a single internal host, hex-like subdomain labels, sequential numeric labels, high query rate to an otherwise unknown TLD.</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </section>
      </div>

      <aside class="side-col">
        <section class="card flag-card">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— submit flag</h2>
          <p class="flag-hint">Format: <code>FOIL&#123;...&#125;</code></p>
          <form id="flag-form" data-hash={challenge.flagHash} data-id={challenge.id} data-pts={challenge.points}>
            <input id="flag-input" type="text" class="flag-input mono" placeholder="FOIL{flag_here}" autocomplete="off" spellcheck="false" />
            <button type="submit" class="flag-submit mono">check →</button>
          </form>
          <div id="flag-result" class="flag-result" aria-live="polite"></div>
        </section>

        <section id="scoreboard-section" class="card sb-card hidden">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— add to scoreboard</h2>
          <form id="sb-form">
            <input id="sb-name" type="text" class="flag-input mono" placeholder="Your handle" maxlength="32" autocomplete="off" />
            <button type="submit" class="flag-submit mono">submit score →</button>
          </form>
          <div id="sb-result" class="flag-result"></div>
        </section>

        <section class="card hints-card">
          <h2 class="card-heading mono">— hints</h2>
          <p class="hint-gate-note mono">Hints unlock progressively as you spend time on the challenge.</p>
          <ol class="hints-list">
            {challenge.hints.map((h, i) => {
              const unlockMins = [5, 10, 20, 30][i] ?? 30
              return (
                <li>
                  <details data-hint-unlock={String(unlockMins)}>
                    <summary class="mono">hint {i + 1}</summary>
                    <p>{h}</p>
                  </details>
                </li>
              )
            })}
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="card meta-card mono">
          <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-k">published</span><span class="meta-v">{challenge.published}</span></div>
          <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-k">author</span><span class="meta-v">{challenge.author}</span></div>
          <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-k">solved</span><span class="meta-v mono" id="solved-status">—</span></div>
          <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-k">time</span><span class="meta-v mono" id="challenge-timer">0:00</span></div>
          <div class="meta-row"><span class="meta-k">rate</span><span class="meta-v"><span class="rating-btns"><button id="btn-up" class="rating-btn" title="Good challenge">👍</button><button id="btn-down" class="rating-btn" title="Needs work">👎</button></span></span></div>
        </section>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </main>

  <script>
    const form = document.getElementById('flag-form') as HTMLFormElement
    const input = document.getElementById('flag-input') as HTMLInputElement
    const result = document.getElementById('flag-result') as HTMLElement
    const flagHash = form.dataset.hash!
    const challengeId = form.dataset.id!
    const challengePts = Number(form.dataset.pts!)
    const timerEl = document.getElementById('challenge-timer')!
    const sbSection = document.getElementById('scoreboard-section')!
    const sbForm = document.getElementById('sb-form') as HTMLFormElement
    const sbResult = document.getElementById('sb-result')!

    const TIMER_KEY = `foillab_start_${challengeId}`
    const SOLVED_KEY = `foillab_solved_${challengeId}`

    function fmtTime(ms: number): string {
      const s = Math.floor(ms / 1000)
      return `${Math.floor(s / 60)}:${(s % 60).toString().padStart(2, '0')}`
    }

    let startTs = Number(sessionStorage.getItem(TIMER_KEY))
    if (!startTs) { startTs = Date.now(); sessionStorage.setItem(TIMER_KEY, String(startTs)) }

    const solvedTime = sessionStorage.getItem(SOLVED_KEY)
    const solvedStatusEl = document.getElementById('solved-status')
    if (solvedStatusEl) {
      solvedStatusEl.textContent = solvedTime ? `✓ ${solvedTime}` : 'not yet'
      if (solvedTime) (solvedStatusEl as HTMLElement).style.color = 'var(--accent)'
    }
    let timerInterval: ReturnType<typeof setInterval> | null = null

    if (solvedTime) {
      timerEl.textContent = solvedTime
    } else {
      timerEl.textContent = fmtTime(Date.now() - startTs)
      timerInterval = setInterval(() => { timerEl.textContent = fmtTime(Date.now() - startTs) }, 1000)
    }

    async function sha256(text: string): Promise<string> {
      const buf = new TextEncoder().encode(text)
      const digest = await crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', buf)
      return Array.from(new Uint8Array(digest), b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0')).join('')
    }

    form.addEventListener('submit', async (e) => {
      e.preventDefault()
      const flag = input.value.trim()
      if (!flag) return
      const hash = await sha256(flag)
      if (hash === flagHash) {
        if (timerInterval) { clearInterval(timerInterval); timerInterval = null }
        const elapsed = fmtTime(Date.now() - startTs)
        sessionStorage.setItem(SOLVED_KEY, elapsed)
        timerEl.textContent = elapsed
        result.className = 'flag-result flag-correct'
        result.textContent = `✓ Correct! Solved in ${elapsed}.`
        sbSection.classList.remove('hidden')
      } else {
        result.className = 'flag-result flag-wrong'
        result.textContent = '✗ Incorrect. Keep digging.'
        input.select()
      }
    })

    if (solvedTime) {
      result.className = 'flag-result flag-correct'
      result.textContent = `✓ Already solved in ${solvedTime}.`
      sbSection.classList.remove('hidden')
    }

    function applyHintGates(): void {
      const elapsedMins = (Date.now() - startTs) / 60000
      document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.hints-list details').forEach((det) => {
        const unlock = Number(det.dataset.hintUnlock ?? 30)
        const remaining = Math.ceil(unlock - elapsedMins)
        if (elapsedMins >= unlock) {
          det.classList.remove('hint-locked')
          det.querySelector('.hint-lock-msg')?.remove()
        } else {
          det.classList.add('hint-locked')
          let msg = det.querySelector('.hint-lock-msg')
          if (!msg) { msg = document.createElement('p'); msg.className = 'hint-lock-msg'; det.appendChild(msg) }
          msg.textContent = `Unlocks after ${unlock} min  (${remaining} min left)`
        }
      })
    }
    applyHintGates()
    setInterval(applyHintGates, 30_000)

    const RATING_KEY = `foillab_rating_${challengeId}`
    const btnUp = document.getElementById('btn-up') as HTMLButtonElement
    const btnDown = document.getElementById('btn-down') as HTMLButtonElement
    function applyRating(r: string | null): void {
      btnUp.classList.toggle('rating-active', r === 'up')
      btnDown.classList.toggle('rating-active', r === 'down')
    }
    applyRating(localStorage.getItem(RATING_KEY))
    btnUp.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const next = localStorage.getItem(RATING_KEY) === 'up' ? null : 'up'
      next ? localStorage.setItem(RATING_KEY, next) : localStorage.removeItem(RATING_KEY)
      applyRating(next)
    })
    btnDown.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const next = localStorage.getItem(RATING_KEY) === 'down' ? null : 'down'
      next ? localStorage.setItem(RATING_KEY, next) : localStorage.removeItem(RATING_KEY)
      applyRating(next)
    })

    sbForm.addEventListener('submit', (e) => {
      e.preventDefault()
      const nameInput = document.getElementById('sb-name') as HTMLInputElement
      const name = nameInput.value.trim()
      if (!name) return
      const key = 'foillab_scoreboard'
      type Entry = { name: string; pts: number; solved: string[]; ts: number }
      const existing: Entry[] = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(key) ?? '[]')
      const idx = existing.findIndex(entry => entry.name.toLowerCase() === name.toLowerCase())
      if (idx >= 0) {
        if (!existing[idx].solved.includes(challengeId)) {
          existing[idx].pts += challengePts
          existing[idx].solved.push(challengeId)
          existing[idx].ts = Date.now()
        }
      } else {
        existing.push({ name, pts: challengePts, solved: [challengeId], ts: Date.now() })
      }
      localStorage.setItem(key, JSON.stringify(existing))
      sbForm.style.display = 'none'
      sbResult.className = 'flag-result flag-correct'
      sbResult.innerHTML = 'Score added! <a href="/lab/scoreboard" style="color:inherit">View scoreboard →</a>'
    })
  </script>
</Layout>

<style>
.challenge-page { padding-top: 40px; padding-bottom: 80px; }
.breadcrumb { font-size: 12px; color: var(--dim); margin-bottom: 32px; }
.breadcrumb a { text-decoration: none; color: var(--dim); }
.breadcrumb a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
.challenge-header { margin-bottom: 40px; }
.header-badges { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 16px; }
h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.subtitle { color: var(--muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; max-width: 600px; }
.two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px; gap: 24px; align-items: start; }
@media (max-width: 860px) { .two-col { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .side-col { order: -1; } }
.card { background: var(--panel); border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 10px; padding: 24px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.card-heading { font-size: 12px; color: var(--dim); font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 18px; }
.scenario-body { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.8; }
.scenario-body strong { color: var(--text); }
.file-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 14px; padding: 14px 16px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.03); border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 8px; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; transition: border-color 0.15s; }
.file-row:hover { border-color: rgba(65,208,127,0.3); }
.file-icon { font-size: 18px; }
.file-info { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px; }
.file-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; }
.file-size { font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); }
.writeup-teaser { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.writeup-reveal summary { cursor: pointer; font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); padding: 8px 0; list-style: none; user-select: none; }
.writeup-reveal summary:hover { color: var(--accent); }
.writeup-content { margin-top: 20px; }
.writeup-content h3 { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text); margin: 20px 0 8px; }
.writeup-content h3:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.writeup-content p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 10px; }
.writeup-content pre { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.4); border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 6px; padding: 14px 16px; overflow-x: auto; margin: 10px 0; }
.writeup-content pre code { background: none; padding: 0; color: var(--accent); font-size: 13px; }
.writeup-content code { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 12px; }
.flag-hint { font-size: 12px; color: var(--dim); margin-bottom: 14px; }
#flag-form { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
.flag-input { width: 100%; background: rgba(0,0,0,0.3); border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 6px; padding: 11px 14px; color: var(--text); font-size: 14px; outline: none; transition: border-color 0.15s; }
.flag-input:focus { border-color: rgba(65,208,127,0.4); }
.flag-submit { background: var(--accent); color: #08090d; border: none; border-radius: 6px; padding: 11px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; transition: opacity 0.15s; }
.flag-submit:hover { opacity: 0.85; }
.flag-result { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; min-height: 20px; text-align: center; margin-top: 8px; }
.flag-correct { color: var(--accent); }
.flag-wrong { color: #ef4444; }
.sb-card #sb-form { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
.hidden { display: none; }
.hints-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; }
.hints-list details summary { font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); cursor: pointer; list-style: none; padding: 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair); user-select: none; }
.hints-list details summary:hover { color: var(--accent); }
.hints-list details p { margin-top: 10px; font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.6; }
.hint-gate-note { font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: 0.02em; }
.hint-locked > summary { pointer-events: none; opacity: 0.45; cursor: default; }
.hint-lock-msg { font-size: 11px; color: var(--dim); margin-top: 6px; font-family: var(--mono); }
.meta-card { padding: 18px 24px; }
.meta-row { display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; font-size: 12px; padding: 6px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hair); }
.meta-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.meta-k { color: var(--dim); }
.meta-v { color: var(--muted); }
.rating-btns { display: flex; gap: 6px; }
.rating-btn { background: none; border: 1px solid var(--hair); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 6px; cursor: pointer; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; transition: border-color 0.15s, background 0.15s; }
.rating-btn:hover { border-color: rgba(65,208,127,0.4); }
.rating-btn.rating-active { border-color: var(--accent); background: rgba(65,208,127,0.1); }
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .challenge-page { padding-top: 24px; padding-bottom: 48px; }
  h1 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
  .subtitle { font-size: 14px; }
  .card { padding: 18px 16px; }
  .writeup-content pre { padding: 10px 12px; font-size: 11px; }
}
</style>
